name: Harees
short_description: Savory and hearty, this centuries-old Omani porridge blends tender meat with coarse wheat, simmered to perfection. A beloved Ramadan staple, it offers a comforting taste of tradition.

name: Luqaimat
short_description: Golden, crispy bites of sweet dough emerge from the fryer, soaking in rich syrup or honey. A beloved treat in Oman, Luqaimat combines fluffy texture with a delightful sweetness, celebrating tradition in every bite.

name: Shuwa
short_description: Often regarded as Oman's national dish, shuwa features marinated lamb or goat, slow-cooked in an underground sand oven. Its rich blend of spices creates an unforgettable, tender flavor experience.

name: Majboos
short_description: Savor the rich flavors of Majboos, a beloved Omani rice dish featuring tender chicken or lamb, fragrant basmati, and a medley of red onion and tomato. Infused with spices, it embodies the culinary heritage of the Arabian Peninsula.

name: Omani halwa
short_description: Gelatinous and sticky, Omani halwa enchants with a blend of saffron, cardamom, and rosewater, celebrating joyous occasions like weddings and Ramadan. Each batch offers a unique flavor experience, crafted with care.

name: Omani Chicken Biryani
short_description: Features fragrant basmati rice layered with tender chicken, zesty lime, and aromatic spices. A beloved dish that marries Indian and Persian influences, it delights with every flavorful bite.

name: Mishkak
short_description: Originating from Oman, skewered mishkak features marinated cubes of tender beef, chicken, or mutton grilled to smoky perfection. Each bite bursts with rich spices, offering a delicious street food experience.

name: Mashuai
short_description: Spit-roasted to perfection, this Omani specialty features kingfish, or kanad, generously rubbed with aromatic spices and oil. A cherished tradition, it offers a savory taste of Omanâ€™s rich culinary heritage.

name: Chicken kabouli
short_description: Savory basmati rice meets tender chicken in this Omani classic, infused with fragrant cardamom, coriander, and cloves. A delightful blend of spices makes every bite a taste of tradition.

name: Madrouba
short_description: Spicy and comforting, this Omani porridge combines tender chicken with overcooked rice and a fragrant blend of turmeric, cumin, and cardamom, creating a warm, soul-soothing dish cherished in Arabian culture.

name: Lokhemat
short_description: Originating from Oman, these delightful deep-fried sweets feature a fluffy dough infused with fragrant cardamom. Golden-brown and irresistibly crispy, they offer a perfect balance of warmth and sweetness.

name: Halawet Ahmad
short_description: A beloved Omani treat, this indulgent dessert features roasted vermicelli enveloped in creamy condensed milk, butter, and almond powder, all topped with a sprinkle of coconut for a delightful finish.

name: Khabeesa
short_description: A beloved Omani comfort food, this fragrant porridge combines creamy milk, nutty semolina, and rich butter, infused with rose water, saffron, and cardamom, then crowned with crunchy fried cashews.
